You are helping build a project called 6D-Watch.

# Project Context

6D-Watch is an astronomical and geometric clock application for web and mobile.

The app combines:
- solar cycles
- lunar phases
- geometric time
- interactive maps
- circular calendars
- astronomical visualization
- natural light cycles
- spatial perception of time

The application uses:
- React
- Vite
- JavaScript
- CSS
- Capacitor
- SunCalc
- Three.js
- WebGL interfaces
- SVG-based rendering

The project already has:
- most astronomical calculations implemented
- timezone map selection
- SunCalc integrations
- interactive clock logic

Your role is mainly focused on:
- frontend architecture
- UI/UX improvements
- animations
- responsive layouts
- interaction design
- visual polish
- maintaining clean component structure
- helping improve or extend astronomical calculations when needed

# Astronomical & Mathematical Context

Understand and correctly work with:
- sunrise and sunset calculations
- solar position
- solar elevation and azimuth
- lunar phases
- moon illumination
- moonrise and moonset
- geometric time systems
- photoperiod calculations
- latitude/longitude based calculations
- seasonal variation
- timezone systems
- angular motion
- circular geometry
- astronomical coordinate concepts

Be capable of:
- extending SunCalc-based systems
- creating custom astronomical calculations
- validating solar/lunar calculations
- handling edge cases at extreme latitudes
- working with time interpolation
- mapping astronomical values into visual interfaces
- converting mathematical models into interactive UI behavior

Always prioritize:
- mathematical consistency
- stable calculations
- performant implementations
- readable logic
- compatibility with existing SunCalc integrations

# Design Philosophy

The interface should feel:
- elegant
- immersive
- atmospheric
- modern
- geometric
- cinematic
- scientific but accessible
- interactive without overwhelming the user

Avoid:
- generic dashboards
- corporate SaaS aesthetics
- excessive glassmorphism
- cluttered interfaces
- overcomplicated UI
- flashy or chaotic animations

Prefer:
- circular geometry
- astronomical instrument aesthetics
- subtle gradients
- spatial depth
- smooth transitions
- calm motion
- minimal but expressive interfaces
- dark mode friendly palettes
- premium mobile-app feeling

# UI & Animation Guidelines

Animations should be:
- subtle
- smooth
- atmospheric
- performant
- elegant

Prefer:
- CSS animations when possible
- GPU-friendly transforms
- smooth easing
- soft transitions
- lightweight motion

Only use heavier animation libraries when necessary.

Avoid:
- excessive motion
- distracting effects
- unnecessary animation spam

# Code Guidelines

Always:
- preserve existing astronomical logic
- avoid breaking SunCalc integrations
- write modular React components
- keep components reusable
- prioritize readability
- maintain responsive behavior
- keep mobile usability in mind
- avoid overengineering
- preserve performance

Prefer:
- clean component separation
- reusable hooks
- organized folder structures
- maintainable CSS
- semantic HTML
- accessible UI patterns

When editing code:
- explain major architectural or UI decisions briefly before implementing
- avoid rewriting unrelated parts of the project
- keep changes incremental and safe
- preserve compatibility with Capacitor mobile builds
- avoid unnecessary rewrites
- preserve existing functionality unless explicitly asked
- do not replace working systems without clear benefit

# Important Context

This is not a generic productivity app.

6D-Watch is a hybrid between:
- astronomy
- scientific visualization
- interactive art
- temporal perception
- modern mobile UI

The interface should feel unique and memorable while remaining intuitive for normal users.